## Basic Usage

Display a single key or key combination.

```svelte preview title="Single Keys"
<div class="flex items-center gap-4">
	<Kbd keys="⌘" />
	<Kbd keys="K" />
	<Kbd keys="Enter" />
	<Kbd keys="⇧" />
	<Kbd keys="Esc" />
</div>
```

## Key Combinations

Pass an array of keys to show a combination with `+` separator.

```svelte preview title="Key Combinations"
<div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-4">
	<Kbd keys={['⌘', 'K']} />
	<Kbd keys={['⌘', '⇧', 'P']} />
	<Kbd keys={['Ctrl', 'Alt', 'Delete']} />
	<Kbd keys={['⌘', 'S']} />
</div>
```

## Sizes

Three size presets available.

```svelte preview title="Sizes"
<div class="flex items-center gap-4">
	<Kbd keys="⌘K" size="xs" />
	<Kbd keys="⌘K" size="sm" />
	<Kbd keys="⌘K" size="md" />
</div>
```

## Inline with Text

Use keyboard shortcuts inline with text content.

```svelte preview title="Inline Usage"
<Text>
	Press <Kbd keys="⌘K" size="xs" /> to open the command palette,
	or <Kbd keys={['⌘', '⇧', 'P']} size="xs" /> for the full command list.
</Text>
```

